  if(length(unique(o)) == 28) {
    break
  }

}

## [1] 97
#1b.
set.seed(2017)
couponCollector <- function(v) {
  o <- vector()
  count <- 1
  repeat {
    o[count] <- sample(v, 1)
    if(length(unique(o)) == 28) {
      break
    }
    count <- count + 1
  }
  return(count)
}
#1c.
v <- c(LETTERS, '!', '?')
lens <- vector(length = 500)
set.seed(2017)
for(i in 1:500) {
  lens[i] <- couponCollector(v)
}
mean(lens)
## [1] 107.9
hist(lens)

My result is 107.9, which is close to 109.9608

#1d.
v <- c(rep(LETTERS, 5), '!', '?')
lens <- vector(length = 500)
set.seed(2017)
for(i in 1:500) {
  lens[i] <- couponCollector(v)
}
mean(lens)
## [1] 208.134
mean(lens) / 107.9
## [1] 1.928953
hist(lens)

My result is 208.134, it’s 1.928953 times of before.
